@node "Overview" "Overview"
Here is a list of LFSystemBinder's features:

    * Powerfully Manage @{b}ASSIGN@{ub}s, @{b}RESIDENT@{ub}s, @{b}DOS VARIABLE@{ub}s and @{b}PATH@{ub}es in a
    very @{i}@{u}intuitive@{ui}@{uu} G.U.I (Graphical User Interface),

    * Use @{b}project file@{ub} for easely installing and removing programs. No more
     tedious change in your User-Startup,

    * Monitor (and change) "@{b}@{u}on the fly@{ub}@{uu}" your system datas using the
     @{b}interactive@{ub} mode (new in version 2.0),

    * Fully @{b}font sensitive@{ub}, @{b}short-keyed@{ub} and @{b}localized@{ub} G.U.I.,

    * @{b}On-line context sensitive@{ub} short @{b}help@{ub} on the windows and extensive help
    using AmigaGuide®,

    * @{b}AppWindow@{ub} and @{b}AppIcon@{ub} support,

    * Very powerful and comprehensive @{b}AREXX port@{ub} (for easely creation of
    projet in an Installer script),

    * Work on @{b}all@{ub} Amiga (under 2.0+) even on a stock Amiga 600 !!

    * more, more, more...

    @{fg shine}@{bg shadow}TRY IT AND YOU'LL LOVE IT!!@{fg text}@{bg back}
@endnode

@node "Why" " Why LFSystemBinder was written ?"
    - You don't know what "User-Startup" means ?
    - CLI, Shell or AmigaDos sound to you like MS-DOS ?
    - You had searched a real ASSIGN manager for long time ?
    - You need an easy way for installing (and removing) applications ?

     LFSystemBinder is for you! You can install new application without using
    tiedous AmigaDos script.
@endnode

@node "System" " System needed "
     @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} run on all AMIGAs under @{" 2.0 or more " link "2.0" 0} and use
    the ReqTools.library 38+. It can be @{" localized " link "localisation" 0} under 2.1+. AREXX port
    doesn't need running REXXMASTE (see @{" LFRxDirect " link "Compagnons" 0} ).

