@node "2.0" "OS 2.0"
     I'm sorry for 1.x user but this @{i}obsolet@{ui} OS isn't supported by
    @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}, mainly because programming system manager for pre-2.0
    system is boring and as my old 1000 is upgraded to 2.1, I haven't any
    more a working 1.3 system.
@endnode

@node "Installing" "Installing"
    All is done by the @{b}installer@{ub} script.

    - Install or update @{b}registry.library@{ub} in your @{b}Libs:@{ub} directory.
    - Copy @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} directory in your HD, w/ selected files for your
        localisation.
    - Install @{b}the selected icon@{ub} (4 or 8 colors).

    Note: Installer 1.24 seems to have a problem for displaying its windows
        if your workbench screen is deeper than 4 colors (incorrect handling
        of colors pens). @{fg shine}@{bg shadow}THIS IS A BUG IN INSTALLER AND NOT IN MY SCRIPT !@{fg text}@{bg back}
@endnode

@node "GUI" " The window"
@next "Menu"
@prev "Main"
     In @{b}LFSystemBinder 2.0@{ub}, you have a short context sensitive help on the
    bottom of the window. For more information, hit @{b}[HELP]@{ub} key for displaying
    the related topic in this file.

     The window is @{b}AppWindow@{ub}:
        - put a projet file and it is added to the actual project,
        - Others icons are added as elements of the current list.

   @{" Type Select         " link "gtype" 0} select the active list.
   @{" Assign Group        " link "Gassign" 0} manage ASSIGN's datas.
   @{" Residents Group     " link "Gresident" 0} manage RESIDENT's datas.
   @{" Remove              " link "GRemove" 0} inverse data meaning (unassign,...).
   @{" Informations Gadget " link "GMsg" 0} some informations about selected item.
   @{" Comment             " link "GCom" 0} allow adding comment to a data.
   @{" List Gadget         " link "GLst" 0} display active list.
   @{" Add " link "GAdd" 0}, @{" Up " link "GUp" 0}, @{" Modify " link "GMod" 0},
   @{" Down " link "GDn" 0}, @{" Delete " link "GSupp" 0},     manage datas in the displayed list.
   @{" Return " link "GRet" 0}, @{" Sort " link "GSrt" 0},
   @{" UnSelect " link "GDs" 0}  &  @{" Grab " link "GGrab" 0}
   @{" Interactive         " link "GInter" 0} Toggle interactive mode.

     Each button has its own short key, showned by an underlined character.
    Example : '@{b}A@{ub}' for @{b}@{u}A@{uu}jouter@{ub}. Notez bien: @{u}Case is meanful@{uu}. For combo boxes
    like assign's confict methode gadget, lower case go to the next value and
    uppers' to previous.

     See also @{" Menu " link "Menu" 0}.
@endnode

@node "gtype" "The list selector"
@toc "GUI"
    Select the list to active.
@endnode

@node "GLst" "The list gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     This gadget display all items in the active list selected using the
    @{" Type Select " link "gtype" 0} gadget.

     If you click once on an @{b}item@{ub}, it becomes selected and its own datas are
    displayed in the @{"information" link "GMsg" 0} and @{"comment" link "GCom" 0} gadgets.

     A star '@{b}*@{ub}' show marked item (for use with @{"use marked" link "MPUseMark" 0} menu for example).
    To toggle this mark, click one more time in the selected item.
@endnode

@node "Gassign" "The assign group"
@toc "GUI"
    Manage attribut of assign items.

   @{" Assign Type       " link "GTass" 0}  Select the ASSIGN's type.
   @{" Conflict Methodes " link "GAConf" 0}  Change the conflict methode.
   @{" All Gadget        " link "GAAll" 0}  Remove all values of a multi-assign?
@endnode

@node "GTass" "Assign's type"
@toc "Gassign"
     All assign type supported by AmigaDos 2.0 can be used:
        - @{b}@{u}Normal Assign@{ub}@{uu} : A physical lock (Lock() form Dos.library) is used.
        - @{b}@{u}Multi Assign@{ub}@{uu} : Like Normal ones but multiple directory are pointed.
        - @{b}@{u}Non-Binding Assign@{ub}@{uu} or @{b}@{u}Path Assign@{ub}@{uu} : Instead of the two first, no
         lock is used, so this type of assign are resolved at each time they
         are referenced.
        - @{b}@{u}Delayed Assign@{ub}@{uu} : This type of assign are created like Non-Binding
         ones but, at the first time they are referenced, they are resolved
         and converted to a normal one.

    See your Amiga Dos manual for more informations...
@endnode

@node "GAConf" "Assign's conflict methode"
@toc "Gassign"
     Select the method for resolving an @{b}@{i}assign conflict@{ub}@{ui}. (i.e. When you ask
    for adding an already existing assign).

     Supported methode are:
        - @{b}@{u}Interactive@{ub}@{uu} : Users are asked for what they want to do,
        - @{b}@{u}Replace@{ub}@{uu} : Newer assign replace olders,
        - @{b}@{u}Add@{ub}@{uu} : Newer assign is added to the older. This action fail if the
         older isn't a normal or a multi assign,
        - @{b}@{u}Safety Add@{ub}@{uu} : First, LFSystemBinder try to add the new data but in
         failure, it tries an '@{b}@{u}Replace@{ub}@{uu}' action.
@endnode

@node "GAAll" "All"
@toc "Gassign"
     This attribut acts with multi-assign.

     When you ask for removing an assign, if this gadget is set, this assign
    is @{u}totally@{uu} removed. If unset, only sub-values in the list of
    @{b}LFSytemBinder@{ub} are removed.

    E.G:
    Original assign in the system:      List of LFSystemBinder
        bidon:                              bidon:
            ->ram:                              ->ram:
            ->t:                                ->sys:
            ->sys:

    Resulting assign in the system:
    With ALL attribut                   Without ALL attribut
        bidon doesn't exist any more.       bidon:
                                                ->t:

     Notez-bien: In this case, bidon becomes a @{b}NORMAL@{ub} assign, but it can be
    totally destroyed if all sub-values are represented in the list.
@endnode

@node "Gresident" "Resident's groupe"
@toc "GUI"
     Manage attributs of @{b}@{i}resident commands items@{ub}@{ui}.

    @{b}@{u}Force@{ub}@{uu} : Doesn't look for @{b}PURE@{ub} attribut of the command (If not set, user
        is asked if you try to make a non-pure command resident). Like
        @{i}RESIDENT PURE@{ui} of AmigaDos.
    @{b}@{u}Delayed@{ub}@{uu} : Make this resident delayed. As far as I know, only @{"CSH" link "CPR" 0} can use
        delayed residents (v5.20+ needed). Those commands became real
        resident commands when they are used for the first time.

     Current CSH version (tested up to v5.39) have a bug. If you want to use
    delayed resident, set environemental variable "@{b}CshResident@{ub}" to "1".
    @{fg shine}@{bg shadow}THIS IS A BUG OF CSH AND NOT OF LFSYSTEMBINDER.@{fg text}@{bg back}
@endnode

@node "GRemove" "Remove attribut"
@toc "GUI"
     @{b}@{i}The meaning of an objet is reversed@{ub}@{ui}. So @{b}ASSIGN@{ub} objets are unassigned,
    @{b}PATH@{ub} are deleted, @{b}VARIABLE@{ub} deleted and RESIDENT unloaded.

    See also @{"Option/Reverse" link "MOInv" 0} menu.
@endnode

@node "GMsg" "Informations gadgets"
@toc "GUI"
     This gadget displays @{b}@{i}informations@{ub}@{ui} about current selected objet. This can
    be the name of the assign for multi-assign, the pointed directory for
    other assign, or the content of a variable.
@endnode

@node "GCom" "Comments gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     You can add a @{b}@{i}comment@{ub}@{ui} to the selected objet with this gadget.
    Don't forget to hit @{b}[Return]@{ub} key for validating your input.
    Comments are totally ignored by the system, and if you are in @{"interactive" link "GInter" 0}
@{"    mode" link "GInter" 0}, all comments are discarded at any notification.

     See @{"Options/Locale/Sort by comment" link "MOLSBC" 0} menu
@endnode

@node "GAdd" "Add gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     @{b}Add@{ub} an objet to the @{b}@{i}current@{ub}@{ui} list.

     The new objet take his attributs from the current status of @{b}@{i}attributs'
    gadgets.@{ub}@{ui}

    NOTE: To use current directory, enter an @{u}empty@{uu} string in a directory
    requester.
@endnode

@node "GUp" "Up gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     The selected objet goes @{b}upper@{ub} in the current list.

     For multi assign sub values or path directory : More an objet is upper
    in the list, more its @{b}@{i}priority@{ub}@{ui} increase.
@endnode

@node "GDn" "Down gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     The selected objet goes @{b}lower@{ub} in the current list.

     For multi assign sub values or path directory : More an objet is upper
    in the list, more its @{b}@{i}priority@{ub}@{ui} increase.
@endnode

@node "GMod" "Modify gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     @{b}Modify@{ub} the name or the content of an object. For modifying object's
    attributs you must first make the objet selected and modify gadgets
    attributs.
@endnode

@node "GSupp" "Delete Gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     @{b}Delete@{ub} the selected object form the current list. If no object is
    selected, a requester allowing you to delete only marked objets or
    the list entirely.

    @{b}@{u}Note:@{ub}@{uu} Use with caution in interactive mode the delete all feature as you
    can destroy all datas without a return way (except rebooting your Amiga
    or recreating all manualy).
@endnode

@node "GInter" "Interactive gadget"
@toc "GUI"
     If this gadget is set, you are in @{b}INTERACTIVE@{ub} mode. In this mode,
    you can manage your system datas "@{i}@{u}on the fly@{ui}@{uu}". E.g, if you select
    @{b}@{i}ENVIRONNEMENTAL VARIABLEs@{ub}@{ui} as current list, you can see all change
    made in global variables by other tasks. More, you are allowed to
    delete or change what you want!
@endnode

@node "GSrt" "Sorting a list"
@toc "GUI"
     @{b}Sort@{ub} the @{b}@{i}current@{ub}@{ui} list in alphabetical order (unusable if you display the
    path's list or a sub assign list).

     If @{"Options/Locale/Sort by comments" link "MOLSBC" 0} is check, your datas are sorted by
    associated comments instead of by name.

     For Residents, pathes are ignored.
@endnode

@node "GHlp" "On line context sensitive help"
@toc "GUI"
     This gadget give you a @{b}short help@{ub} about GUI element where the mouse
    pointer is.
@endnode

