        @{"Path" link "MOPGO" 0}
            @{"Only Global" link "MOPGO" 0}
            @{"Replace" link "MOPGO" 0}
        @{"Always Force Residents" link "MOAFR" 0}
        @{"Locale" link "MOLoc" 0}
            @{"Sort by comments" link "MOLSBC" 0}
            @{"No Delayed Residents" link "MOLNDR" 0}
            @{"4 Colors icons" link "MOL4" 0}
@endnode

@node "MPNew" "Project/New : Clear all"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Clear@{ub} all datas and all attributs are set to there @{b}default@{ub} values.
@endnode

@node "MPLoad" "Project/Load : Load a project file"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Load@{ub} a project file. @{b}@{u}CAUTION:@{ub}@{uu} Current datas aren't erased but news one
    are added.

     Loading an @{b}LFSystemBinder 1.0@{ub} project file may display a requester.
    NOREQ tools'type force @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} to be @{b}@{i}quiet@{ub}@{ui}" link "NOREQ" 0}
tools'type force LFSystemBinder to be quiet.
@endnode

@node "MPSave" "Project/Save : Save a project file"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Save@{ub} a datas file. By default a @{b}@{i}8 colors icon@{ub}@{ui} is created using MagicWB's
    palette but you can choose a standard 4 colors icon using
    @{"Options/Locale/4 colors icon" link "MOL4" 0} menu. If an icon exist for this file, it
    isn't overwritted.
@endnode

@node "MPUse" "Project/Use : Use datas"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Activate@{ub} current data: Assign are created, variables setted, Residents
    commands loaded and path modified.

     Object with @{"reverse" link "GRemove" 0} attribut are destroyed.

     @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} If menu @{"Options/Remove" link "MOInv" 0} is set, all @{"Remove" link "GRemove" 0} attributs are reversed,
    so for uninstalling a program you just have to set @{"Options/Remove" link "MOInv" 0}.
@endnode

@node "MPUseMark" "Project/Use Marked: Use marked datas"
@toc "Menu"
     Same as @{"Project/Use" link "MPUse" 0} but only marked objets are activated.
@endnode

@node "MPCD" "Project/Set Home Directory"
@toc "Menu"
     Change the @{b}current directory@{ub} of LFSystemBinder. It can be used whenever
    a directory is need by entering an @{u}empty@{uu} string.

     When you load a project file, the current directory is set to where this
    file reside in.
@endnode

@node "MPIcon" "Project/Iconify"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Iconify@{ub} LFSystemBinder. Double-click on its AppIcon sitting on the
    Workbench's windows for reopening.

    @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} The LFSystemBinder's windows always open on the @{b}@{u}CURRENT@{ub}@{uu} default
    public screen.
@endnode

@node "MPInfo" "Project/Info"
@toc "Menu"
     Display an @{b}informations requester@{ub} showing compilation's date for each
    module and the name of the AREXX port.
@endnode

@node "MPImp" "Project/Print"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Print@{ub} current datas in a file ('PRT:', your printer, by default).
@endnode

@node "MPQuit" "Project/Quit"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Quit@{ub} LFSystemBinder. You are asked for a confirmation if some datas
    stills unsaved.
@endnode

@node "MEMarkAll" "Edition/Mark All"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Mark@{ub} all objects in the currently showned list.
@endnode

@node "MEUnMarkAll" "Edition/Unmark All"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Unmark@{ub} all objects in the currently showned list.
@endnode

@node "METogAss" "Edition/Toggle assign"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Toggle@{ub} the mark of a multi-assign.
@endnode

@node "MOInv" "Options/Reverse"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Reverse@{ub} the meaning of all objets in this file (objets qualified by
    remove are created, the others are delete).
@endnode

@node "MOAss" "Options/Assign"
@toc "Menu"
     You can choose the default methode for @{b}resuming an assign conflict@{ub}.
    This default methode is used for all assign qualified by '@{"Interactive" link "GAConf" 0}'
    methode.
     If all item of this sub-menu are unchecked, a requester is showned when
    an conflict occure.
@endnode

@node "MOPGO" "Options/Path"
@toc "Menu"
     @{b}Global Path Only:@{ub} If this item is checked, only the @{b}@{i}global@{ub}@{ui} path (stored
    in the "Workbench" process structure) is modified, else pathes for all
    CLI processes are affected.

     @{b}Replace:@{ub} The new path @{b}@{i}replace@{ub}@{ui} the older (else it is added).
@endnode

@node "MOAFR" "Options/Always force residents"
@toc "Menu"
    If checked, all resident commands are @{"forced" link "Gresident" 0}.
@endnode

@node "MOLoc" "Options/Locale"
@toc "Menu"
     This sub-menu store @{b}@{i}locales options@{ub}@{ui}: They aren't saved in datas' file
    and are only used in edition.

    @{"Sort By Comments" link "MOLSBC" 0}
    @{"No Delayed Residents" link "MOLNDR" 0}
    @{"4 Colors Icons" link "MOL4" 0}
@endnode

@node "MOLSBC" "Options/Locale/Sort by comments"
@toc "MOLoc"
     Instead of sorting by @{b}objets' name@{ub}, if this item is checked, lists
    are @{b}sorted by comments@{ub}.
@endnode

@node "MOLNDR" "Options/Locale/No Delayed Residents"
@toc "MOLoc"
     Forbid use of @{"delayed" link "Gresident" 0} residents. If checked, residents qualified as
    delayed are used as normal residents.

    Set this options if you don't use CSH. see @{"NODELAYED" link "NODELAYED" 0} tools'type.
@endnode

@node "MOL4" "Options/Locale/4 Colors Icons"
@toc "MOLoc"
     By default, datas'files are created with @{b}8 colors icons@{ub} (ŕ la MagicWB),
    but they look very ugly on 4 colored Workbench (as used on my old
    A1000!). If you check this item, @{b}@{u}4 colors icons@{ub}@{uu} are created.
@endnode

@node "AREXX" "AREXX"
@next "TTypes"
@prev "GUI"
     @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} have an AREXX port named by default "@{b}LFSystemBinder.rdv@{ub}"
    (it can be changed usimg @{"RXPORT" link "RXPORT" 0} tools'type).

     This AREXX port is @{u}aviable and running@{uu} even if @{b}@{i}RexxMaster@{ub}@{ui} isn't running
    or if AREXX's related libraries (@{i}rexxsupport.library@{ui} &
    @{i}rexxsyslib.library@{ui}) aren't loadable by using my @{"LFRxDirect" link "Compagnons" 0} tool (included
    in this distribution) or CSH's @{b}rxsend@{ub} command. So you can use
    LFSystemBinder as compagnon of @{b}Installer@{ub} on very small system.

    @{"NEW" link "RXNEW" 0}ą    : Reset all datas
    @{"ADD" link "RXADD" 0}     : Add an object to the current list
    @{"DELETE" link "RXDELETE" 0}  : Delete marked objets
    @{"MARK" link "RXMARK" 0}    : Mark objets
    @{"UNMARK" link "RXUNMARK" 0}  : Unmark objets
    @{"GRAB" link "RXGRAB" 0}ą   : Grab current system's datas
    @{"FREE" link "RXFREE" 0}ą   : Delete entirely a list content
    @{"SHOW" link "RXSHOW" 0}    : Select the list to display
    @{"SORT" link "RXSORT" 0}ą   : Sort list's objets
    @{"SET" link "RXSET" 0}     : Modify certains attributs
    @{"SAVE" link "RXSAVE" 0}    : Save datas
    @{"LOAD" link "RXLOAD" 0}ą   : Load a datas file
    @{"CD" link "RXCD" 0}      : Change the current directory
    @{"PRINT" link "RXPRINT" 0}   : Print current datas to a file
    @{"USE" link "RXUSE" 0}ą    : Activate current's datas
    @{"ICONIFY" link "RXICONIFY" 0} : Iconify LFSystemBinder
    @{"INTERACTIVE" link "RXINTERACTIVE" 0} : Activate or desactivate the interactive mode
    @{"QUIT" link "RXQUIT" 0}    : Quit LFSystemBinder

        ą Commands unaviables in interactive mode.


    @{u}NOTES:@{uu}
    - The orders of optionnal arguments like @{b}REMOVE@{ub} isn't meanfull. So
        ADD RESIDENT c:Echo FORCE NONDELAYED @{b}NONREMOVE@{ub}
    and
        ADD RESIDENT c:Echo @{b}NONREMOVE@{ub} FORCE NONDELAYED
    are identic to LFSystemBinder,
    - If opposites attributs are present in the same commands line, like
    @{b}REMOVE@{ub} and @{b}NOREMOVE@{ub}, only the last is meanfull,
    - Comments must be the last argument
    - LFSystemBinder AREXX parser isn't case sensitif BUT Arexx translate
    all unquoted text to upper cases. @{u}Notez-bien:@{uu} All Exec's list ARE case
    sensitives so "Machin" and "machin" aren't the same ARexx port.
    - As space and TAB are considered as separators, string using such
    characters must be quoted.
    - The current directory must be passed as an empty string (""),
    "Current Directory" isn't accepted and will hurt localised LFSystemBinder!
@endnode

@node "RXNEW" "ARexx Command: NEW"
@toc "AREXX"
     @{b}Reset all datas@{ub}: Clear lists, all menus are reseted to there initiales
    values (see @{"tools'type" link "TTypes" 0}).
@endnode

@node "RXADD" "ARexx Command: ADD"
@toc "AREXX"
    ADD ASSIGN <name> <path> [NORMAL|DELAYED|PATH] [INTER|REPLACE|ADD|SAFETY]
            [ALL|NONALL] [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    ADD VAR <name> <contents> [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    ADD RESIDENT <command> [FORCE|NONFORCE] [DELAYED|NONDELAYED]
            [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    ADD PATH <path> [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]


     @{b}Add@{ub} an objet to the given list. If an attribut isn't given, it will
    take its value from the GUI.
@endnode

@node "RXDELETE" "ARexx Command: DELETE"
@toc "AREXX"
    DELETE ASSIGN|VAR|RESIDENT|PATH|ALL

     @{b}Delete@{ub} marked elements of the given list. See @{"MARK" link "RXMARK" 0} and @{"UNMARK" link "RXUNMARK" 0}.
@endnode

@node "RXMARK" "ARexx Command: MARK"
@toc "AREXX"
    MARK ASSIGN|VAR|RESIDENT|PATH <objet> [<objet> ...]

     @{b}Mark@{ub} objets in the selected list. <objet> can use standard AmigaDos
    wildcard. i.e.:
        MARK ASSIGN D#?
    or
        MARK ASSIGN D*
    mark all assign starting by D.
@endnode

@node "RXUNMARK" "ARexx Command: UNMARK"
@toc "AREXX"
    UNMARK ASSIGN|VAR|RESIDENT|PATH <objet> [<objet> ...]

     @{b}Unmark@{ub} objets in the selected list. <objet> can use standard AmigaDos
    wildcard. i.e.:
        UNMARK ASSIGN D#?
    or
        UNMARK ASSIGN D*
    unmark all assign starting by D.
@endnode

@node "RXGRAB" "ARexx Command: GRAB"
@toc "AREXX"
    GRAB ASSIGN <name> [NORMAL|DELAYED|PATH] [INTER|REPLACE|ADD|SAFETY]
            [ALL|NONALL] [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    GRAB VAR <name> [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    GRAB RESIDENT <command> [FORCE|NONFORCE] [DELAYED|NONDELAYED]
            [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

    GRAB PATH [REMOVE|NONREMOVE] [<comment>]

     @{b}Grab@{ub} system's datas according to <name>. <name> can be use standard
    AmigaDos wildcard.  If an attribut isn't given, use the current
    configuration of the GUI's gadget.
@endnode

@node "RXFREE" "ARexx Command: FREE"
@toc "AREXX"
    FREE ASSIGN
    FREE VAR
    FREE RESIDENT
    FREE PATH

    @{b}Clear@{ub} the given list. Associed attributs aren't modified.
@endnode

@node "RXSHOW" "ARexx Command: SHOW"
@toc "AREXX"
    SHOW ASSIGN
    SHOW VAR
    SHOW RESIDENT
    SHOW PATH

        @{b}Select@{ub} the list to display.
@endnode

@node "RXSORT" "ARexx Command: SORT"
@toc "AREXX"
    SORT ASSIGN
    SORT VAR
    SORT RESIDENT

     @{b}Sort@{ub} (and display) the given list.
    According to @{"Options/Locales/Sort by command" link "MOLSBC" 0} menu, the sort is done by
    name or by comments.
@endnode

@node "RXSET" "ARexx Command: SET"
@toc "AREXX"
    SET REVERSE ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET ASSIGN INTER|REPLACE|ADD|SAFETY|DEFAULT
    SET PATHGLOBALONLY ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET PATHREPLACE ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET RESFORCE ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET NODELAYED ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET COMSORT ON/OFF/DEFAULT
    SET ICON4 ON/OFF/DEFAULT

     @{b}Set@{ub} or @{b}unset@{ub} an option. @{b}@{i}DEFAULT@{ub}@{ui} mean return to the default value done
    by @{"tools'types" link "TTypes" 0}.
@endnode

@node "RXSAVE" "ARexx Command: SAVE"
@toc "AREXX"
    SAVE <file_name>

     @{b}Save@{ub} current datas to a file.
@endnode

@node "RXLOAD" "ARexx Command: LOAD"
@toc "AREXX"
    LOAD <file_name>

     @{b}Load@{ub} a datas-file.
@endnode

@node "RXCD" "ARexx Command: CD"
@toc "AREXX"
    CD <directory>

     @{b}Select@{ub} the current work directory.
@endnode

@node "RXPRINT" "ARexx Command: PRINT"
@toc "AREXX"
    PRINT [<out_file> [<header>]]

     @{b}Print@{ub} datas to <out_file> ("PRT:" by default).
@endnode

@node "RXUSE" "ARexx Command: USE"
@toc "AREXX"
    USE ASSIGN [MARKED]
    USE VAR [MARKED]
    USE RESIDENT [MARKED]
    USE PATH [MARKED]
    USE ALL [MARKED]

     @{b}Activate@{ub} datas of the given list. With @{b}@{i}MARKED@{ub}@{ui}, only ... @{"marked" link "RXMARK" 0} datas
    are activated.
@endnode

@node "RXICONIFY" "ARexx Command: ICONIFY"
@toc "AREXX"
    ICONIFY ON|OFF

     @{b}Iconify@{ub} or not LFSystemBinder.
@endnode

@node "RXQUIT" "ARexx Command: QUIT"
@toc "AREXX"
    QUIT

     @{b}Quit@{ub} LFSystemBinder.
@endnode

@node "RXINTERACTIVE" "ARexx Command: INTERACTIVE"
@toc "AREXX"
    INTERACTIVE ON|OFF

     Go to or come from @{"interactive" link "GInter" 0} mode.
@endnode

@node "TTypes" "Tools'types"
@prev "AREXX"
     The following tools'types allow the user to configure @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}.
    They can be classed in 2 groupes:

     - Tools'types only allowed in LFSystemBinder's icon:
    @{"PGMNAME" link "PGMNAME" 0}    indicate the default tool of projects.
    @{"GUIDE" link "GUIDE" 0}      indicate the name of the AmigaGuide datas base
    @{"ICONIFY" link "ICONIFY" 0}    LFSystemBinder must start iconifyed
    @{"RXPORT" link "RXPORT" 0}     indicate the name of LFSystemBinder's AREXX port
    @{"NOREQ" link "NOREQ" 0}      discard some requester
    @{"COMSORT" link "COMSORT" 0} and @{"ICON4" link "ICON4" 0} configure somes items of options menu

     - Tools'type for both LFSystemBinder's or projects' icons:
    @{"ASSIGN" link "TTASSIGN" 0}, @{"PATHREPLACE" link "PATHREPLACE" 0}, @{"PATHGLOBALONLY" link "TTPGO" 0}, @{"RESFORCE" link "RESFORCE" 0}, @{"NODELAYED" link "NODELAYED" 0}, @{"REVERSE" link "REVERSE" 0}.
    In LFSystemBinder's icon, used to @{b}configure@{ub} somes items of options menu;
    in projects icon, used to @{b}force@{ub} associated options, as if the project was
    saved with related items of the options menu checked.

     If you are a SHELL user, those tools'type can be passed as arguments
    to @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}. i.e.:

        @{i}LFSystemBinder ICONIFY RXPORT=Mon_Port@{ui}
@endnode

@node "PGMNAME" "PGMNAME Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     By using '@{b}PGMNAME@{ub}' tools'type, you can overwrite the "@{b}@{i}default tool@{ub}@{ui}" of
    newly created projects.

    Example:
        @{i}PROGNAME=sys:prefs/lfSystemBinder@{ui}
@endnode

@node "ICONIFY" "ICONIFY Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     This tools'type force LFSystemBinder to start @{b}iconified@{ub}.
@endnode

@node "NOREQ" "NOREQ Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}NOREQ@{ub}' tools'type is usefull for using @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} as AREXX client
    @{b}installer@{ub} like programme, by discarding some requesters:
        - Confirmation when datas are modified,
        - force an assign to normal type,
        - modification of an already existing variable,
        - adding many time an object to a list,
        - non pure and non forced commands aren't made resident.
@endnode

@node "RXPORT" "RXPORT Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     By using '@{b}RXPORT@{ub}' tools'type, you can set the AREXX message port of
    @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} (by default the port name is "@{b}@{i}LFSystemBinder.rdv@{ub}@{ui}").

    Example:
        @{i}RXPORT=LFSB_myport@{ui}
@endnode

@node "COMSORT" "COMSORT Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}COMSORT@{ub}' tools'type set by default value of
     "@{"Options/Locale/Sort By Comments" link "MOLSBC" 0}".
@endnode

@node "ICON4" "ICON4 Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}ICON4@{ub}' tools'type is used to create, by default @{b}4 colors@{ub} icon for
    projects instead of 8 colors.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Locale/4 Colors Icons" link "MOL4" 0}").
@endnode

@node "GUIDE" "GUIDE Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     with '@{b}GUIDE@{ub}' tools'type, you can specify where @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} can find
    its @{u}AmigaGuide documentation data base@{uu} (this file).

    Example:
        @{i}GUIDE=Doc:LFSystemBinder.guide@{ui}
@endnode

@node "TTASSIGN" "ASSIGN Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}ASSIGN@{ub}' tools'type set the default value of the default assign conflict
    methode.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Assign" link "MOAss" 0}")

    Possibles values:
@{i}        ASSIGN=REPLACE
        ASSIGN=ADD
        ASSIGN=SAFETY@{ui}
@endnode

@node "NODELAYED" "NODELAYED Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}NODELAYED@{ub}' tools'type disable by default use of delayed resident.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Locale/No Delayed Residents" link "MOLNDR" 0}")
@endnode

@node "REVERSE" "REVERSE Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}REVERSE@{ub}' tools'type reverse by default the meaning of all objects.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Reverse" link "MOInv" 0}").
@endnode

@node "RESFORCE" "RESFORCE Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}RESFORCE@{ub}' tools'type force by default residents commands.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Always force residents" link "MOAFR" 0}").
@endnode

@node "TTPGO" "PATHGLOBALONLY Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     If '@{b}PATHGLOBALONLY@{ub}' tools'type is present only the global path (stored
    in the "@{b}@{i}Workbench@{ub}@{ui}" process structure) is modified, else pathes for all
    CLI processes are affected.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Path/Global Path Only" link "MOPGO" 0}").
@endnode

@node "PATHREPLACE" "PATHREPLACE Tools'type of LFSystemBinder's and projects'icon"
@toc "TTypes"
     '@{b}PATHREPLACE@{ub}' tools'type means path datas in this project @{b}replace@{ub} the
    current system's one. If not present, new datas are added.
    (set the default value of "@{"Options/Path/Replace" link "MOPGO" 0}").
@endnode

@node "Examples" "Examples"
     I'm sorry but i don't have time to make a real tutorial for this
    tool. Have a look to "@{b}Examples@{ub}" directory where you can find some usefull
    examples.
@endnode

@node "Questions" "F.A.Q"
    @{i}@{u}* How can I access to the @{b}currect directory@{ub} ?@{ui}@{uu}
    -> It's very easy: The resulting string of a directory requester must be
    @{b}empty@{ub}. (Right-Amiga + 'X' and 'Return' for cleaning string's gadget)

    @{i}@{u}* How can i @{b}merge@{ub} two project files ?@{ui}@{uu}
    -> Since the very early ß version of LFSystemBinder 1.0, you can merge
    projects ! The only thing you do is to load the first project, then the
    second, then the 3rd, ... When you load a data file LFSystemBinder
    @{b}doesn't erase@{ub} current datas but @{b}adds@{ub} the new ones to the olders.

    @{i}@{u}* Why LFSystemBinder can't '@{b}Mount@{ub}' peripherals or @{b}launch@{ub} programs ?@{ui}@{uu}
    -> Launching isn't the goal of @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}. I think using AmigaDos'
    scripts is a very better solution for such thing.
    -> Mounting new device is done by AmigaDos' "@{b}MOUNT@{ub}" command. I don't have
    any information about mounting. Instead, use OS2.1+ facilities by using
    small mount-list and icons. See your WB manual.

    @{i}@{u}* I need a @{b}060@{ub} version for my turbo board !@{ui}@{uu}
    -> Different versions for powered processors aren't useful for such
    tools, as @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} is very @{u}CPU non-consoming@{uu}. I made test with my
    040 Amiga4000 and 000 and 040 versions haven't significant differences
    timing (on the same machine). Perhaps PowerPC Amiga needs a special
    version ?

    @{i}@{u}* Goodies introduced in LFSystemBinder 2.0, like @{b}notifications@{ub}, on line@{ui}@{uu}
    @{i}@{u}help, aren't time consoming ?@{ui}@{uu}
    -> @{b}@{u}No@{ub}@{uu} because NO CODE in LFSystemBinder is '@{i}Busy Waiting@{ui}' (i'm not
    micro-sucker !). @{"PatchAssign" link "Installing" 0} only redirect some system functions and send
    notifications when such calls are made. It's doesn't scan every time
    system's lists for change... Some developpements and tests have been made
    on my old Amiga1000, using a 68010 7 Mhz CPU (+15% / A2000), and
    @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} works fine on it!

    @{i}@{u}* Will LFSystemBinder 3.0 make coffee ?@{ui}@{uu}
    -> ...
@endnode

@node "TecNotes" "Technicals notes"
    - This tool have been intensively tested on my @{b}Amiga 4000@{ub} with enforcer
    and mungwall. On the other hand, some program may allocate their datas
    in a non-standard way so if you experience GURU using @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} and
    @{b}?XY?@{ub} program, you have a problem with @{b}?XY?@{ub} and not with @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}!
    (@{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} have been tested for 6 months in working environnements
    and no crachs occure ... but in other way, only micro-sucker say that
    there tools aren't buggy. So i just say no bug have been found after
    extensives ßtests !!). Send me a report about this and i'll search if i
    can or i can't secure my tools with ?XY?.

    - Some version of '@{"reqtools.library" link "CPR" 0}', like 38.1042, cause an enforcer
    hits when reading a directory by @{b}rtFileRequest()@{ub} with flags
    @{b}FREQF_SELECTDIRS@{ub} and @{b}FREQF_NOFILES@{ub}. No problem with version 38.1210.
@endnode

@node "Version" "Version"
     This is a @{b}@{u}short@{ub}@{uu} history of @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}. Have a look to Historique
    @{"file" link "Historique/main" 0} for a full bugs fixes, improvements list (but only in french).

    @{b}@{u}LFSystemBinder 2.0:@{ub}@{uu}
    - Interactive mode,
    - Multiple selections in list,
    - AmigaDOS wild-card for selecting and capturing,
    - full support of CSH's delayed residents,
    - On-line position sensitive help,
    - New AREXX commands SELECT and UNSELECT.

    @{b}@{u}LFSystemBinder 1.1:@{ub}@{uu}
    - Use AppIcon and a resizeable AppWindows,
    - Actions can be reversed,
    - Short-Keyed GUI,
    - manage CSH's delayed resident,
    - can create icons ŕ la Magic-Worbench.

    @{b}@{u}Future:@{ub}@{uu}
    - PowerPC version for future Amigas,
    - version for multi-platform Amiga OS (AmigaOS project),
    -...

     This need, perhaps this need a port to GCC and C++...
@endnode

