@node "Compagnons" "Compagnons"
    Following tools are shipped with @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub}:

    - @{b}Register.library@{ub} and @{b}PatchAssign@{ub} : Used for making interactive mode.
    (I'm sorry but complet package of this (very ?) useful library is not
    included because I haven't finished documentation... a boring task isn't
    it ?).

    - @{b}LFRxDirect@{ub} : Send an AREXX command to a client, even if RexxMast isn't
    running,

    - @{b}LFGrabPath@{ub} : This shell command sets its own CLI process path by
    grabbing the global one (stored in the Workbench structure).
@endnode

@node "localisation" "Localization"
     English is the default language of @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} but, if you're using
    WB 2.1+, others can be used (@{u}french@{uu} catalog is included in this
    distribution). Description file (LFSystemBinder.cd) is included for
    adding new catalogs (but think to send me a copy for next releases).

     @{b}LFSystemBinder@{ub} use intelligent short-keying:
    - For gadget, a '@{b}@{u}_@{ub}@{uu}' in the caption indicate that the next key is the
    short key. Note, this is case-sensitif so '@{b}@{u}a@{ub}@{uu}' and '@{b}@{u}A@{ub}@{uu}' can be the short
    keys of 2 differents gagdets (except for cycling gadgets where
    capitalised letters inverse rolling sense).
    - For menu, place the short key, a @{b}NULL@{ub} character (ASCII $00 and not
    $30), then the caption. Example:
       @{i} ?\0About...@{ui}
    define '@{b}?@{ub}' as the short key of menu 'About...'.

    LFSystemBinder warns you about 2 gadgets using the same short key.

    Using a short key for '@{"Delete" link "GSupp" 0}' button is not a good idea i think.
@endnode

